The paper discusses the integration of audio and visual information in perceptual decision-making, which is a topic that falls under the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the potential pitfalls in designing artificial cognitive systems, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SD).
